  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Solanaceae herbaceous perennial (cultivated as annual) native to Andean uplands (2,000–4,000 m elevation, Peru/Bolivia). Produces underground stem tubers (swollen stolons) as primary carbohydrate storage. Alloployploid genome (4x, 2n=48). Purple and blue pigmented cultivars accumulate high-anthocyanin tuber flesh (delphinidin-based). Insect-pollinated, self-fertile; true seed propagation rare, vegetative propagation via seed-tuber the standard.",
